{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 14:52:30.846074", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and approach\n- Verified end-to-end reachability between hosts and server farm.\n- Targeted latency tests (ICMP pings) from multiple vantage points.\n- Measured application-layer timing (HTTP) from hosts.\n- Inspected DNS server’s interface queuing/TC settings and socket listeners.\n\nKey findings\n1) DNS latency anomaly (primary issue)\n- Symptom: All traffic to/from the DNS server (10.200.0.2) shows a consistent ~1 second added delay, sometimes up to ~2 seconds on first packet.\n  - Example ICMP:\n    - host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server: RTT ≈ 1002–1003 ms (3/3 received)\n    - host_2_1_1_1 -> dns_server: RTT ≈ 1003–1011 ms (3/3 received)\n    - dns_server -> load_balancer: 2003 ms then ~1001 ms subsequent pings (3/3 received)\n- Application impact confirmed via HTTP timing (curl) from both hosts:\n  - name lookup ≈ 1.00–1.08 s consistently for web0.local and web99.local\n  - connect occurs almost immediately after lookup (connect timestamp includes DNS), total time ≈ 2.0–3.2 s where ~1 s is attributable to DNS.\n  - Examples:\n    - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://web0.local: namelookup ~1.00–1.08 s; total ~2.01–3.19 s\n    - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://web99.local: namelookup ~1.00 s; total ~2.07–2.09 s\n    - host_2_1_1_1 -> http://web0.local: namelookup ~1.01 s; total ~2.10–2.20 s\n    - host_2_1_1_1 -> http://web99.local: namelookup ~1.00 s; total ~2.07–2.11 s\n- Device-level evidence on dns_server:\n  - tc qdisc on eth0:\n    - qdisc netem 806e: root ... delay 1s\n    - Statistics: Sent 1946 bytes 25 pkt (dropped 0), matching observed test traffic\n  - ip addr shows eth0 using qdisc netem; interface is UP with expected IP 10.200.0.2/24.\n  - netstat confirms DNS service listening on 10.200.0.2:53 and loopback ports as expected.\n\nConclusion for finding #1:\n- Anomaly: Elevated latency specifically tied to DNS server traffic.\n- Localization: dns_server, interface eth0.\n- Root cause: An intentional traffic control (tc netem) configuration applying a 1-second egress delay on dns_server eth0, adding ~1 second to every DNS exchange and inflating overall web access times.\n\n2) General IP reachability and routing health (normal)\n- All tested endpoints (hosts, web servers, load balancer, DHCP) show 0% packet loss and low RTTs outside of DNS paths.\n  - Examples:\n    - host_1_1_1_1 -> web_server_1/2/3: RTT ≈ 1.5–5 ms range\n    - host_2_1_1_1 -> web_server_1/2/3: RTT ≈ 3–16 ms (occasional single-digit-ms spikes; not persistent)\n    - Hosts inter-reachability (10.1.1.10 <-> 10.2.1.10): RTT ≈ 1.6–1.7 ms, 0% loss\n    - Hosts -> load_balancer: RTT typically a few ms (occasional jitter observed but not persistent)\n- No packet loss or path asymmetry detected.\n- OSPF/routing appears functional end-to-end given consistent successful reachability across areas and subnets.\n\n3) Service accessibility (design expectations)\n- Public web servers (web_server_0..3) are reachable by design.\n- Load balancer (web99.local) is reachable and serves content; HTTP performance after DNS resolution is normal.\n- No evidence that backend web servers (behind the load balancer) are directly exposed to hosts based on available host list and tests.\n\nImpact assessment\n- The 1-second tc delay on dns_server adds ~1 second to each DNS query/response, causing user-perceived slowness for name-based access.\n- Web page loads show ~2+ seconds total where ~1 second is attributable solely to DNS. Multi-domain pages may incur multiple ~1-second penalties.\n\nSummary\n- Anomaly detected: Yes — systemic DNS latency.\n- Fault localization: dns_server (eth0) due to tc netem delay 1s.\n- Root cause: Misconfigured or leftover traffic control (netem) on DNS server causing fixed 1-second egress delay, inflating DNS query times and end-user web access latency.\n- Broader network health: Normal. No routing or reachability faults observed; services otherwise reachable and performing as expected once DNS completes.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10199, "output_tokens": 3155, "total_tokens": 13354, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7168}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2048}}}
